The paper proposes a stochastic gradient-based method for solving graph-structured sparsity constraint problems, which is a common problem in machine learning and optimization. The paper also discusses the efficiency and effectiveness of the proposed algorithm through extensive experiments. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
